Just a couple of suggestions and Good luck.<br>
<br>
Ragluv Arcanist/ 44th Tier'Dal mage/ Prexus/ Legions <p>"Life is just a game that should be played to personal preference... After all your going to lose in the end anyway, so enjoy yourself." - Unknown author</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubrene.showPublicProfile>Brene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(6/12/00 7:39:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=30.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Looking for a place to level </span><hr size=1> Frontier mountains, just NW of the castle.. there is a safe area there that nothing wanders through. Just west of there is a TON (and I mean a TON) of blues/yellows (brutes, rockshapers etc). There is a &quot;T&quot; shaped rock there, with a tree to the East of it. I have my pet sit there, and pull from the rock, or right below the rock. Most creatures there are pretty slow, so you wont take a beating there. Drag it back to the safe spot and blast away =)<br>
<br>
Forget Giants.. waste of mana. They have over 1000 HP's more then everythiing else in the zone (that you can/should be soloing). not worth it IMO. <p>Brene<br>
