They're in the little hut on the hill, named Ascania Halfbin and Larrisa Gelrith (sp?). Anyway, it drops faction with various important factions, but it is easily gained back by stuffing that greedy dwar...err... Doing the Muffins for Pandos quest.<br>
<br>
Breaking the spawn can be challenging, med up to full, get a nice earth pet, BO II, swords of runes, buff yourself with Phantom Chain (or was it leather?), and your current Shielding. Make sure you're at full mana, then damage shield the both of you. Send pet at Ascania, then target Larissa and Nuke her on to you, then hammer /pet back off once it hits with a root, and finish Larissa, then wait as much as you can before finishing Ascania, and presto, you have a split spawn. You'll have to fight every 3mins to keep it split, and keeping up can get difficult, but the loot and experience is SO worth it.<br>
<br>
Just remember a few things. <br>
Never run to the sisters if a greenie pirate attacks you. Theres a bug and the sister that hits for 300+ will kill you.<br>
Bind yourself on the Island.<br>
Leave before you get KoS and do the muffins quest, then come back.<br>
<br>
You might die a few times breaking the spawn (I did), but keep at it and it becomes easy.<br>
